    lyrics: 'Lord of Peace,\n\nAs I lay my head down tonight, my mind is still running. Thoughts of tomorrow, worries of today, memories of the past — all fighting for space in my weary mind.\n\n"He grants sleep to those He loves." — Psalm 127:2\n\nI receive Your gift of rest right now. I hand You every thought that keeps me awake. I give You every worry that steals my peace. I trust that while I sleep, You are still working.\n\nGuard my sleep. Keep nightmares far from me. Let my rest be deep and restorative. Let me wake refreshed and ready for tomorrow.\n\n"I lie down and sleep; I wake again, because the Lord sustains me." — Psalm 3:5\n\nThank You for the night. Thank You for rest. Thank You for being my peace.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Prayer for Broken Relationships', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '💔', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'Father of Reconciliation,\n\nThis relationship is broken and I do not know how to fix it. Words were spoken that cut deep. Trust was shattered. The distance between us feels impossible to cross.\n\nYou are the God who makes all things new. You are the God who restores. Nothing is beyond Your ability to heal — not even this.\n\nIf this relationship can be restored, I ask You to make a way. Soften hearts. Create opportunities for honest conversation. Replace bitterness with compassion, pride with humility.\n\nIf it cannot be restored, give me the grace to forgive anyway. Give me the strength to release the pain. Protect me from a bitter heart.\n\n"Be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, as God in Christ forgave you." — Ephesians 4:32\n\nHeal us, Lord. Start with me.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Prayer for Financial Stress', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '💰', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'Provider God,\n\nThe financial pressure is crushing me. Bills pile up, needs go unmet, and I do not know where the provision will come from.\n\nBut You are Jehovah Jireh — the God who provides. You fed 5,000 with five loaves and two fish. You sent ravens to feed Elijah. You have never let Your children starve.\n\n"My God will meet all your needs according to the riches of His glory in Christ Jesus." — Philippians 4:19\n\nI trust this promise today. Open doors of provision I cannot see. Give me wisdom to steward what I have. Remove the spirit of fear and replace it with faith.\n\nHelp me not to worry about tomorrow, but to trust You one day at a time.\n\nYou are my Provider. I rest in that truth today.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Prayer for Forgiveness of Self', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '🕊️', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'Merciful Father,\n\nI struggle to forgive myself. The mistakes I have made replay in my mind. The shame I carry is heavy. I feel like I do not deserve Your grace.\n\nBut Your Word declares: "There is therefore now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus." — Romans 8:1\n\nHelp me to receive what You have already declared. You have forgiven me completely. You have removed my sin as far as the east is from the west. You remember it no more.\n\nWhy then do I keep punishing myself for what You have already forgiven?\n\nHelp me to extend to myself the same grace You so freely give. Help me to silence the voice of shame with the truth of Your Word.\n\nI am forgiven. I am free. I am Your beloved child.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Morning Healing Affirmations', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '🌅', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'Today I declare over my life:\n\n✝️ I am loved by God unconditionally.\n✝️ I am strong because God is my strength.\n✝️ I am healed by the stripes of Jesus.\n✝️ I am not defined by my past.\n✝️ I am not my anxiety, my depression, my fear.\n✝️ I am a child of the Most High God.\n✝️ The same power that raised Jesus from the dead lives in me.\n✝️ No weapon formed against me shall prosper.\n✝️ This day is a gift and I will walk through it with grace.\n✝️ God goes before me, beside me, and behind me.\n\n"I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me." — Philippians 4:13\n\nThis is who I am. This is whose I am. Today I choose faith over fear.\n\nAmen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Prayer for Strength in Trials', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '💪', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'Lord of all strength,\n\nI am going through a trial that is testing everything in me. My faith feels thin, my strength is gone, and I cannot see the end of this tunnel.\n\nBut Your Word says: "Consider it pure joy, my brothers and sisters, whenever you face trials of many kinds, because you know that the testing of your faith produces perseverance." — James 1:2-3\n\nHelp me to find joy in this season — not because the trial is good, but because You are using it to build something beautiful in me.\n\nI don\'t ask You to remove this trial if it is building my character. I just ask for the strength to endure it with grace. Hold me up when I want to give up. Remind me of Your promises when I forget.\n\nYou will not waste my pain. You are working all things together for good.\n\nI trust You, Lord.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Prayer for Children with Special Needs', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '👶', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'Father God,\n\nI bring before You my precious child — wonderfully and fearfully made by Your hands. Created with purpose, loved beyond measure, seen by You completely.\n\nIn a world that does not always understand my child, remind me that You created them intentionally. There is no mistake in how they are made. You have a plan and purpose specifically for them.\n\nGive me supernatural wisdom as their parent. Give me patience that does not run dry. Give me creativity to find what reaches their heart.\n\nSurround them with the right teachers, the right friends, the right helpers. Open every door they need opened. Close every door that would harm them.\n\nLet them know they are loved — by You and by me — completely and without condition.\n\n"Before I formed you in the womb I knew you." — Jeremiah 1:5\n\nThank You for this precious gift.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
  Song(title: 'Prayer for Addiction Recovery', artist: 'Devotional', emoji: '🔓', category: 'Therapy & Healing',
    lyrics: 'God of Freedom,\n\nI come to You in honesty today. I struggle with something that has control over me. This addiction has stolen so much — my health, my relationships, my dignity.\n\nBut You are a God who sets captives free. "So if the Son sets you free, you will be free indeed." — John 8:36\n\nI cannot break this chain on my own. I have tried and failed. But I believe You can do what I cannot.\n\nBreak the power of this addiction over my life. Remove the craving. Replace the void it fills with Your presence. Give me the courage to seek help and the strength to stay the course.\n\nHelp me take one day at a time. One hour at a time if that is what it takes.\n\nYou did not bring me this far to leave me. You are my Deliverer.\n\nIn Jesus\' name, Amen. 🙏'),
];
